indicator.description:
1.	Number of sub-projects launched;
2.	Number of beneficiary organizations; 
3.	Types of requested activities
4.	Number of sub-projects stimulating a follow-up capacity development  initiatives 
5.	Effectiveness/impact of the GRF activities (i.e. trainings, strategies, recommendations, etc.) measured by individual objective criteria
6.	Feedback by senior management of organizations on the outcomes of sub-projects

target.comment:
1. At least four capacity development sub-projects launched; 
2. At least six agencies are direct beneficiaries of Governance Reform Fund (GRF);
3. Requested activities facilitate continuous/sustainable capacity development of the agencies (Yes/No);
4. At least one initiative stimulated follow up activities/reforms in agencies;
5.1. Objective evaluation criteria developed for each sub-project/activity;
5.2. At least 75% of evaluation criteria met;
5.3. Outputs of the sub-project contribute to implementation of reforms and/or transformational change within agencies;
6. Positive feedback received form agency's senior management (Yes/No)

actual.comment:
1.1. Four capacity development sub-projects were launched in 2014;
2.1. Six agencies were direct beneficiaries in 2014: 
* Ministry of Foreign Affairs of Georgia (MFA);
* National Centre for Education Quality Enhancement (NCEQE);
* Educational Management Information System (EMIS);
* Ministry of Labour, Health and Social Affairs (MoLHSA);
* LEPL 112
* Public Service Development Agency (PSDA); 
3.1. Yes, all the sub-projects made emphasis on linkage between specific initiatives to strategic priorities at national or agency level; promotion of evidence-based decision making and long-term strategic planning; support of activities like implementation of policies, development of strategic papers, ToTs, training module development, etc;
4.1. One sub-project launched in 2014 has stimulated significant follow-up activities. Specifically, the PSDA sub-project led to the formation of the Innovative Service Lab, which was outside of the original vision of the initiative. Through the Lab, the PSDA has continued to encourage innovation in public services beyond the scope of the project. 
5.1.Evaluation criteria were developed and agreed upon at the proposal stage for each sub-project and activity;
5.2. At least 75% of evaluation criteria was met;
5.3. According to the selection criteria for sub-projects and consultancies, all activities are aligned with national reform priorities and contribute to capacity-building in agencies; 
6.1. Yes, evaluation interviews and letters of appreciation received from senior beneficiaries indicate positive reactions to all initiatives launched in 2014.

