actual.comment:
1.1. Three capacity development sub-projects were launched in 2015; 
2.1. Three beneficiary agencies were supported: the Civil Service Bureau (CSB), Ministry of Corrections (MoC), and Ministry of Environment and Natural Resource Protection (MENRP). 
3.1. Yes; all the sub-projects made emphasis on linkage between specific initiatives to strategic priorities at national or agency level;
4.1. In 2015, two sub-projects led to additional activities and reforms within the beneficiary agencies. Following the completion of a sub-project to raise awareness on whistleblower protection among civil servants at the central level, a new initiative has been launched to raise awareness at the local government level; Within MoC through its Penitentiary and Probation Training Center, policy development and the development of training materials through the sub-project has led to the launch of a comprehensive training program in September 2015. 
5.1. Evaluation criteria were developed and agreed upon at the proposal stage for each sub-project and activity;
5.2. Evaluation of the initiatives is in progress; the results will be presented during the next reporting period.
5.3. All activities are aligned with national reform priorities and contribute to capacity-building in agencies.
6.1. Yes, evaluation interviews and letters of appreciation received from senior beneficiaries indicate positive reactions to all initiatives launched.

