target.comment:
1. Sustainable Pasture Management Planning initiated;
2. Baseline Carbon Stock Inventory conducted
3. At least 2 pilots for local livelihood improvement identified;
4. At least 2 pilot farms identified to test best practices of sustainable pasture management;
5. Inter-ministerial policy debate on pastures management issues initiated on national level.

actual.comment:
a) Preparation of Sustainable Pasture Management Plan for Vashlovani Protected Areas kicked off;
b) Best practices of sustainable pasture management identified for piloting in two farms;
c) Local livelihood assessment which identifies the needs of the Tush shepherds was conducted. According to the survey, one of the main concerns is the absence of unified veterinary service. Introduction of such service planned: additional survey carried out in order to identify the type of service, location and estimate potential “service consumers”, mobilize stakeholders, prepare cost-estimates;
d) In order to establish a long-term pasture monitoring system in the context of climate change and ensure continuous data flow on climatic parameters such as precipitation, air temperature, humidity, atmospheric pressure, wind speed etc. two automatic meteorological stations have been purchased which will be installed within the territory of the VPAs. 
e) Carbon inventory of pasturelands, general soil fertility assessment and water balance modelling was carried out; 
f) Facilitation of a high-level dialogue on the issues of pastures management in the country was launched. High-level conferences brought together the representatives of the Government and international organizations to share experience, information and coordinate on the issues of pastures management;
g) Works to introduce natural flow based water supply system launched in order to rehabilitate/lift off pressure from migratory route within VNP

target.comment:
1. Sustainable Pasture Management Plan finalized;
2. At least 15 Sheep Farms (at least 60 shepherds) with improved livelihood;
3. At least 2 pilot farms set up for sustainable pasture management demonstration;
4. 200 ha of the Migratory route improved

